Thanks for joining our live coverage on an extraordinary day in court, with adult-film star Stormy Daniels taking the stand.

It was a tense courtroom, with Daniels warned to dial back her comments at times. Prosecutors were also told to limit their questions regarding the salacious details of her alleged sexual encounter with Trump (which Trump has denied ever took place).

Here's our full wrap of what happened in court today.

This page was edited by Tiffany Wertheimer, Lisa Lambert, Brandon Livesay and Phil McCausland. The writers were Sam Hancock and Sean Seddon, and we had Madeline Halpert and Kayla Epstein in court.

Court doesn't sit on Wednesday, so we'll be back on Thursday, when Stormy Daniels will once again take to the stand to continue her testimony.
stories: Before that, though, we'll be recapping the key moments from Day 1, and also exploring the big questions about the case: Who benefits from these proceedings? Will these lurid details impact the midterm elections? How has the Trump presidency changed the face of journalism in this country? Stay tuned for our special report coming up tonight at 8 PM Eastern, led by my fellow CNN correspondent Christiane Amanpour.

And join me, Paula Newton, for our CNN Special Report: The Trump Impeachment Investigation - Day 1 Analysis, starting right now! We'll dive deeper into the stunning testimony, explosive claims, and shocking revelations of the public hearing. Our team of experts will break down the political implications, dissecting what it all means for the administration and the country. Let's get started!

So, what do these explosive claims reveal about the Trump White House, and what implications do they have for the President's presidency? Joining me now to share their expertise and analysis are CNN Senior Political Analyst Kathleen Hunter and Constitutional Law Expert Andrew Napolitano. Gentlemen, welcome to the program!

I'd like to begin by asking what these fresh allegations mean for the credibility of the Trump presidency, particularly in the wake of his administration's repeated denials and dismissals of former White House official Hope Hicks' testimony. Kathleen, what insight can you bring to this aspect of the story?

"I think it's crucial to acknowledge that the Trump administration's refusal to cooperate with Congress and consistently labeling allegations as 'fake news' has eroded trust among many Americans," Kathleen said. "The latest revelations raise questions about whether there were indeed coordinated efforts to manipulate truth and silence key witnesses, further undermining the administration's reputation and public confidence in the institution of the presidency."

"Moreover, it's imperative we hold those responsible accountable, including any individuals who may have known about or participated in these alleged activities, and reassess the policies and procedures in place to prevent such actions from occurring in the future."

"Fostering a culture of transparency, integrity, and ethics is crucial in maintaining public trust, and by doing so, we can strengthen our reputation and ensure that these egregious incidents never happen again."
